fields.Title: WHIRLING F2 / MEDICINE CABINET
fields.Description:
Klaasje's medicine cabinet.
1) Find speed (Saint-Batiste goodstuff)
2) Find barbiturates, benzos, SOS and narcan
3) check to steal speed if kim there

fields.Title: Suggestion: "Be honest. He's not grilling you, h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Be honest. He's not grilling you, he just wants to know. Ask if he's ever wanted to take it too.

fields.Title: You: "Look at the medications."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look at the medications.

fields.Title: You: "Search the bottles."
fields.Dialogue Text: Search the bottles.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant does not pursue the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant does not pursue the subject further, looking out the bathroom window instead.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Right. Thank you for this informat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right. Thank you for this information." He seems satisfied. "Should we go?"

fields.Title: You: "Search for the Preptide again."
fields.Dialogue Text: Search for the Preptide again.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Interesting. That's used for diamo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Interesting. That's used for diamorphine overdoses..." The lieutenant nods -- then looks at the door.

fields.Title: You: ""Honesty, it makes me the detective..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Honesty, it makes me the detective I am. Have you thought of taking it too?"

fields.Title: You: ""It has no effect on my performance..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It has no effect on my performance, I just take it to feel good."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Pity."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pity.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""There's always a price..." He look..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's always a price..." He looks out the window.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Nah, pig..." the kid says looking..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nah, pig..." the kid says looking around like a young wolf. "That'd been too easy. Let's keep looking."

fields.Title: You: "Just take it in plain sight."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just take it in plain sight.

fields.Title: You: "Keep it to yourself."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep it to yourself.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Right." He seems satisfied with yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right." He seems satisfied with your answer. "I can see how that can be useful."

fields.Title: You: "Search the pill sheets."
fields.Dialogue Text: Search the pill sheets.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Mhm," the lieutenant nods. "She ce..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mhm," the lieutenant nods. "She certainly had her priorities straight when she was packing."

fields.Title: You: ""It keeps me going -- in the short..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It keeps me going -- in the short run."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Hmh." He lets out a little pensive..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmh." He lets out a little pensive hum... "That's what I thought. Let's go?"

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "You could say he's on the *lookout*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You could say he's on the *lookout*.

fields.Title: Authority: "Yes, take it... and then dispose of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, take it... and then dispose of it! This den of narcomania cannot be allowed stand!

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "NACRA? This is used to treat opioid..."
fields.Dialogue Text: NACRA? This is used to treat opioid overdoses. Always handy to have around.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I was just curious. Anyway let's g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I was just curious. Anyway let's go."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "So... the good lieutenant was looki..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So... the good lieutenant was looking for an edge, was he?

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Who cares, man? Who cares what the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Who cares, man? Who cares what the stiff thinks? You got it. Here comes the afterburner! Just put it in your sweaty little hand now...

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "A bright orange bottle with PREPTID..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A bright orange bottle with PREPTIDE stamped on it. In sunny, happy letters! Jackpot, baby! That's the stuff you're looking for! Your palms begin to sweat just holding that little plastic container.

fields.Title: You: "(Whisper.) "NACRA, opioid antagonis..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Whisper.) "NACRA, opioid antagonist."

fields.Title: You: "Take it -- in secret."
fields.Dialogue Text: Take it -- in secret.

fields.Title: Medicine Cabinet: "Feels like gold in your hands. Ligh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Feels like gold in your hands. Light and precious.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Wow. That's unbelievably orange. *A..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wow. That's unbelievably orange. *Anyone* can see that. It's practically *effervescent*!

fields.Title: Medicine Cabinet: "The medicine cabinet has been clean..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The medicine cabinet has been cleaned out. Nothing remains, not one pill or bottle.
fields.Alternate1: The medicine cabinet is empty. Not even a toothbrush.

fields.Title: You: ""She's really cleaned this out.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "She's really cleaned this out."

fields.Title: You: "[Close the cabinet.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Close the cabinet.]

fields.Title: Perception (Smell): "It's clean of chemical odours too...."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's clean of chemical odours too. Just some dried toothpaste on the handle.

fields.Title: Medicine Cabinet: "Among some foreign -- probably Mess..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Among some foreign -- probably Messinian, or Gottwaldian -- marked red blister packs you find... what *do* you find? This is going to take a little know-how.

fields.Title: You: "(Whisper.) "What's NACRA?""
fields.Dialogue Text: (Whisper.) "What's NACRA?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant glances at the rows..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant glances at the rows of pills -- then at the door.

fields.Title: You: "Is there something more interesting..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Is there something more interesting here?

fields.Title: You: ""I understand it's unbecoming but i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I understand it's unbecoming but if I don't perform this job well I am nothing. It's the price I pay."

fields.Title: Medicine Cabinet: "You're just talking to your reflect..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're just talking to your reflection in the cabinet doors now... Things are not good with you.

fields.Title: Medicine Cabinet: "Pill bottles rattle like bones as y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pill bottles rattle like bones as you search the cabinet: paracetamol, histaperidol, something in a foreign language you can't read... Behind them: an unusually shaped nasal spray. Its label reads 'NACRA'.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks toward the doo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks toward the door as if he didn't see you pilfer that sweet Preptide.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Of course you were." He nods. "How..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course you were." He nods. "How does that work anyway?"

fields.Title: You: ""Narcomania is a disease, lieutenan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Narcomania is a disease, lieutenant."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "There is little condescension in hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is little condescension in his phrasing, more measured curiosity.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Smart chick." The kid nods. "Cuno..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Smart chick." The kid nods. "Cuno never leaves shit behind either. Cuno's a pro."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "There it is, the orange sun wearing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There it is, the orange sun wearing blister pack. You feel almost *nostalgic* for it.

fields.Title: Logic: "Probably Garte's work. After she wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Probably Garte's work. After she was arrested.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "But not for scrubbing blood off til..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But not for scrubbing blood off tiles -- or anything else interesting, it seems.

fields.Title: You: "What's so exciting about this orang..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What's so exciting about this orange bottle?
fields.Alternate1: What was so exciting about the orange bottle?

fields.Title: You: ""What are you talking about? I don'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you talking about? I don't take amphetamine, don't be *ludicrous*!"
fields.Alternate1: "What are you talking about? I'm not a narcomaniac, don't be *ludicrous*!"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Hmh." He lets out a little pensive..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmh." He lets out a little pensive hum. "Thought so. Let's go?"

fields.Title: You: ""Looking like a beast in heat is a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looking like a beast in heat is a serious downside, yes."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I thought so." He seems satisfied..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I thought so." He seems satisfied with the answer. "Should we go?"

fields.Title: You: ""There's quite the collection in he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's quite the collection in here."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""An opioid receptor antagonist. It'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "An opioid receptor antagonist. It's used for diamorphine overdoses."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "You dropped it. Smack dab in the mi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You dropped it. Smack dab in the middle of the floor! There it is -- orange as the midsummer evening's sun, or the lieutenant's bomber jacket.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "...nothing of note. The further you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...nothing of note. The further you look the more arcane it gets. You don't know what the rest of this stuff does.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "The beating he took must be more se..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The beating he took must be more serious than he lets on.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes, but... did you know you don't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, but... did you know you don't *have* radiation sickness?"

fields.Title: Medicine Cabinet: "This medicine cabinet is full of wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This medicine cabinet is full of wares -- sheets of pills haphazardly stacked one on top of the other. There's also a toothbrush somewhere in there.

fields.Title: Medicine Cabinet: "It's been used. Quite a lot."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's been used. Quite a lot.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Preptide -- a euphemism for pharma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Preptide -- a euphemism for pharmaceutical amphetamine. Prescription speed."

fields.Title: You: "Pick it up -- but secretly."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pick it up -- but secretly.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I always took you for more of a dr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I always took you for more of a drunk than a chemical abuser," he says as though it's self-evident. "Anyway."
fields.Alternate1: "I always took you for more of a drunk than a chemical abuser, lieutenant-yefreitor," he says as though its self-evident. "Should we go?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "This toothbrush belongs to someone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This toothbrush belongs to someone who doesn't give a damn about her teeth.

fields.Title: You: ""Lieutenant, I also see a brand cal..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lieutenant, I also see a brand called 'Preptide.'"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Maybe I should?" He lets out a lit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe I should?" He lets out a little pensive hum, rubbing his shoulder...

fields.Title: Drama: "It's not insincere. He's actually g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's not insincere. He's actually giving it thought.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "It's speed, man! Just what you were..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's speed, man! Just what you were looking for. They call it *dextroamphetamine* and talk about psychological disorders, but what we're seeing here is some scientifically advanced trucker speed!

fields.Title: Medicine Cabinet: "This medicine cabinet is stocked wi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This medicine cabinet is stocked with drugs, plus an old toothbrush, and...

fields.Title: Interfacing: "You dropped it. Smack dab in the mi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You dropped it. Smack dab in the middle of the floor! There it is -- orange as the midsummer evening's sun.

fields.Title: You: "Look at the toothbrush."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look at the toothbrush.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "And your chest swells with pride --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And your chest swells with pride -- look! It's made right here in Revachol, by Saint-Batiste, a proud Revacholian pharmaceutical company with great *traditions*!

fields.Title: Interfacing: "He did, though. He totally did and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He did, though. He totally did and now he thinks less of you. Should have kept it *sub rosa*.

fields.Title: You: ""Nah, man, the jaw grinding and the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nah, man, the jaw grinding and the sweating -- that's the best part. Shows the medicine is working."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes, that does sound dangerous now..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, that does sound dangerous now that I think about it."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Feels so sleek and beautiful -- you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Feels so sleek and beautiful -- you got it! Here comes the afterburner! Time to become a super-detective again, Harry! Just put it in your sweaty little hand now...

fields.Title: Authority: "Filthy narco! And look -- it's made..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Filthy narco! And look -- it's made right here in Revachol, by Saint-Batiste. A disgraceful pharmaceutical company attempting to lure people into the gutter. You should destroy it!

fields.Title: You: "[Close the cabinet.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Close the cabinet.]

fields.Title: You: ""I was kinda hoping the *gift* woul..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I was kinda hoping the *gift* would be in here."

fields.Title: You: ""How does what work?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "How does what work?"

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Amphetamine -- does it make you a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Amphetamine -- does it make you a better detective?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Anything of note?" he asks in a lo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Anything of note?" he asks in a lowered voice.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "The fuck are you waiting for, let's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The fuck are you waiting for, let's get super fucking PREPPIE!!!

fields.Title: You: "[Close the cabinet.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Close the cabinet.]

fields.Title: You: ""I'm too high on pyrholidon to noti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm too high on pyrholidon to notice. Before you ask -- pyrholidon is used for radiation sickness."

fields.Title: Medicine Cabinet: "The cabinet is cleaned out, emptied..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The cabinet is cleaned out, emptied.

fields.Title: Medicine Cabinet: "Pharmaceuticals line the shelves. S..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pharmaceuticals line the shelves. Sheet upon sheet and pill bottle next to pill bottle: acetylic acid, APAP, eye drops, blood thinners...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant *tries* to keep his..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant *tries* to keep his eyes on the door, but the Preptide bottle sounds like a rattlesnake -- it's basically a percussion instrument that you're stuffing into your pocket.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It may be -- but I asked if it mak..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It may be -- but I asked if it makes you better at your work?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Doesn't the... pupils and the gurn..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Doesn't the... pupils and the gurning jaw, the sweating... doesn't it become tiring after a while?"

fields.Title: You: ""It gives me fiery visions. A windo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It gives me fiery visions. A window into the heart of things."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Right. I'll give it some thought."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right. I'll give it some thought." He seems satisfied with your answer. "Should we go?"

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Who cares, man? Who cares what the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Who cares, man? Who cares what the stiff thinks? Here comes the afterburner! Just put it in your sweaty little hand now...

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Silently the bottle slides into you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Silently the bottle slides into your palm, then -- as you turn -- into your pocket.

fields.Title: You: "Pick it up."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pick it up.

fields.Title: You: ""Better? No. It makes me worse.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Better? No. It makes me worse."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Hmh." He lets out a little pensive..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmh." He lets out a little pensive hum. "Thought so. Let's go?"
